architectural standards. The integration tests provide high confidence in the behavioral correctness of the gating mechanism.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is solid and meets all acceptance criteria. The addition of `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` is a valuable regression anchor for the render pipeline.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v001.md:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/verify/v002.md:- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, whil