bolic novelty peaks (from CCH-034) must align with audio novelty peaks within ±500 ms<br/>- catches cases where symbolic metrics look fine but synthesis flattens expression |\\\\n-| 40 | T-040 | Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCH-040 | — | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |\\\\n+| 33 | T-033 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCS-032 | — | - `tools/sample_library_import.py` script reads a TOML manifest of source files + intended tags and inserts them into the library<br/>- supports both single-file and directory imports<br/>- preserves provenance (original path, captured-by) in `SampleRecord` extras<br/>- 100+ samples land in the library with accurate tags<br/>- tests cover the importer with a small fixture manifest |\\\\n \\\\n-**Sprint 6 total:** ~18 hrs\\\\n+**Sprint 6 total:** ~6 hrs\\\\n \\\\n ---\\\\n \\\\n ## Summary\\\\n \\\\n - **Sprint 1 (Versioning System):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\\\\n-- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 8 tasks, ~24 hrs\\\\n-- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\\\\n+- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 3 tasks, ~12 hrs\\\\n+- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~36 hrs\\\\n - **Sprint 5 (Library & CRUD Polish):** 9 tasks, ~27 hrs\\\\n-- **Sprint 6 (Stretch Goals):** 3 tasks, ~18 hrs\\\\n+- **Sprint 6 (Stretch Goals):** 1 tasks, ~6 hrs\\\\n \\\\n-**Total: 40 tasks, ~129 hours**\\\\n+**Total: 33 tasks, ~111 hours**\\\"}\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183