ement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-031** [T1] Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-032** [T1] Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-033** [T1] Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-034** [T1] Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-035** [T1] Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-036** [T1] Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-037** [T1] Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-024** [T1] Define `SampleRecord` dataclass with sample-id, path, source, character tags, pitch, duration, captured-at, arc context, RMS, peak, transient density. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-025** [T1] Define controlled `CHARACTER_TAGS` vocabulary (warm, metallic, wind, pulse, voice, mechanical, water, sustained, transient, percussive, harmonic, noisy). (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-026** [T1] Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-027** [T1] Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-028** [T1] Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-029** [T1] Add `sw_sampler` to `SIGNATURE_VOICES` quintet in `artist_identity.py` and update `VOICE_ROLES` so a `\\\\\\\"sampler\\\\\\\"` role maps to `\\\\\\\"sw_sampler\\\\\\\"`. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-030** [T1] Add `sampler_density` field (0.0–1.0) to `ArtistMode` with mode-specific values: solitary 0.7, companion 0.25, working_ambience 0.10, evening_reflection 0.65, storm 0.45. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-031** [T1] Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = \\\\\\\"sw_sampler\\\\\\\"`, `voice.role = \\\\\\\"sampler\\\\\\\"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-032** [T1] Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n \\\\n *Subtotal: ~27 hours*\\\\n \\\\n@@ -80,18 +75,16 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\\\\n \\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\\\\n \\\\n-- **T-038** [T2] Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. (~6h)\\\\n-- **T-039** [T2] Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. (~6h)\\\\n-- **T-040** [T2] Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. (~6h)\\\\n+- **T-033** [T2] Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. (~6h)\\\\n \\\\n-*Subtotal: ~18 hours*\\\\n+*Subtotal: ~6 hours*\\\\n \\\\n ---\\\\n \\\\n ## Requirements Coverage\\\\n \\\\n-- **MUST requirements:** 37/37 covered\\\\n-- **SHOULD requirements:** 3 included as stretch\\\\n+- **MUST requirements:** 32/32 covered\\\\n+- **SHOULD requirements:** 1 included as stretch\\\\n \\\\n **✓ All MUST requirements covered.**\\\\n \\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/task-graph.md b/sdp/task-graph.md\\\\nindex 541f6b7..f7cc1bc 100644\\\\n--- a/sdp/task-graph.md\\\\n+++ b/sdp/task-graph.md\\\\n@@ -1,8 +1,8 @@\\\\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer — Task Graph\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument — Task Graph\\\\n \\\\n-**Generated:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.335643+00:00\\\\n-**Total tasks:** 40\\\\n-**Estimated effort:** ~129 hours\\\\n+**Generated:** 2026-04-25T18:39:59.551260+00:00\\\\n+**Total tasks:** 33\\\\n+**Estimated effort:** ~111 hours\\\\n \\\\n ---\\\\n \\\\n@@ -10,16 +10,16 @@\\\\n \\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\n-| 1 | T-001 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-010 | — | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\\\\n-| 2 | T-002 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-011 | — | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; author