 — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → \\\\\\\"warm\\\\\\\"; narrow-band high-centroid → \\\\\\\"metallic\\\\\\\"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → \\\\\\\"sustained\\\\\\\"; transient_density>3/sec → \\\\\\\"percussive\\\\\\\"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → \\\\\\\"harmonic\\\\\\\"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |\\\\n+| 9 | T-009 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-018 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |\\\\n+| 10 | T-010 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-019 | — | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |\\\\n \\\\n **Sprint 1 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\n \\\\n@@ -29,16 +29,11 @@\\\\n \\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\n-| 11 | T-011 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-030 | T-001 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\\\\n-| 12 | T-012 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-031 | T-001 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\\\\n-| 13 | T-013 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-033 | T-001 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\\\\n-| 14 | T-014 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-034 | T-001 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |\\\\n-| 15 | T-015 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-035 | T-001 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\\\\n-| 16 | T-016 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-036 | T-001 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via sci