ncludes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\\\\n-| 2 | T-002 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-011 | — | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\\\\n-| 3 | T-003 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-012 | — | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\n-| 4 | T-004 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-013 | — | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen +