le metadata (`leader`, `follower`, `solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"file_path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:05:49.677Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"write_file_1776398749510_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:05:55.470Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I've completed the verification report and will now commit it to the repository as instructed.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:05:55.507Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1776398755507_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"git add \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" && git commit -m \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"verify(T-024@20260416T181925Z): inde