 or credentials are involved or exposed.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-documented with docstrings and comments explaining the pricing logic. Tests provide comprehensive coverage of all core functions and the CLI. `CHANGELOG.md` has been updated with detailed notes.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No blocking issues found.\n- [ ] (Note) Full test suite `pytest tests/ -x` fails due to pre-existing macOS Seatbelt restrictions on daemon tests that attempt to write to `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is unrelated to T-032. Dedicated tests for this task (`tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` and `tests/test_sdp_telemetry_cost_model.py`) pass 100%.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and the resulting report provides exactly the visibility requested. The decision to interpret \"7+ consecutive days\" as \"7 most recent active days\" was correct given the calendar gaps in the telemetry data.\n"}}

