docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:4:**To:** sdp-cli maintenance agent
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:8:This report consolidates four bugs and one process issue discovered in sdp-cli during production use on CypherClaw. All findings are backed by evidence from the runtime state DB. Fix #1 has already been pulled in (`98da2b4`). The rest are open.
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:76:Also: a task should track which `(lead, verify)` pairs it has already tried, and never retry the same pair within a single run. Evidence from the log shows `gemini/claude -> claude/codex` — both `claude/codex` and `gemini/claude` had already been tried.
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:180:The integrity checker runs as part of the verify phase and treats format violations identically to semantic failures. A task that adds correct code without a docstring gets the same "ESCALATED" verdict as a task that produces broken code.
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:184:Split verify outcomes:
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:202:The default systemd unit shipped with sdp-cli templates (and used on both CypherClaw and likely CTTickets) executes:
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:205:exec sdp-cli orchestrate --start-phase development --end-phase development
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:212:Update the systemd unit template in the sdp-cli project scaffold:
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:216:exec sdp-cli orchestrate --start-phase development --end-phase development
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:219:exec sdp-cli run
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:222:And add to the sdp-cli docs: "For unattended systemd-managed runners, use `sdp-cli run`. Reserve `orchestrate` for interactive use where a human watches the output."
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:278:All five of these queries can be run on any sdp-cli project for comparison. I expect CTTickets shows similar patterns but in lower volume.
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:284:Bug 1 was the gnarly one because it was silent. The other four are all cases where the pipeline is *telling us* something is wrong (ESCALATED verdicts, retry counts, integrity failures) but the mechanism for responding is either too slow (#4) or treats different failures identically (#2, #5). Fixing these turns sdp-cli from a system that burns compute when things go wrong into one that diagnoses and adapts.
